    "All classifications exhibited exceptional accuracy rates, with the highest obtained in HC versus AD.",
    "In particular, the HC versus AD classification yielded an accuracy of 99% when utilizing only the ADNI dataset, and a slightly lower accuracy of 98% when combined the ADNI and non-ADNI datasets.",
    "CNNs are highly valuable in facilitating automatic individual patient diagnosis across the AD continuum.",
    "Despite the diversity of imaging techniques and scanners, without any prior feature engineering this strategy performed effectively.",
    "Clinical diagnosis and algorithm performance can be improved by a longer clinical follow-up."
